Tyler "The Working Man" Hughes waits to be announced as winner of a professional boxing match against Gary Prince on Sunday at the D&N Center in North Platte. (Derek Noehren / The North Platte Telegraph) Ryan "Main Event" MacDonald 
Ryan "Main Event" MacDonald exchanges punches with Luis Avila during a professional boxing match on Sunday at the D&N Center in North Platte. (Derek Noehren / The North Platte Telegraph) Posted: Sunday, October 4, 2015 8:43 pm | Updated: 9:07 pm, Sun Oct 4, 2015. Hughes TKO's Prince in Fight for FlatRock By Derek Noehren dnoehren@nptelegraph.com nptelegraph.com 
Professional boxing returned to North Platte for the first time in over six years as the Fight for FlatRock took center stage on Sunday at the D&N Center. 
In the main event, local boxing legend Tyler "The Working Man" Hughes won via technical knockout in the fourth round over Gary Prince after the referee stopped the fight following Hughes’ fourth knockdown of the fight and third of the round.   Need an account? Create one now. Subscription required
